
What is Bash?

Bash is widely used shell or command-line-interpreter
Bash was released in 1989 and is named Bourne Again SHell

Using a Terminal

A shell runs in a terminal


General Command Syntax

ls -h(option) usr/bin(arguments) 

What are commands

Commands are programs that are available on a system
When we run a command, the system takes a specific action
Many commands have short names in order to save typing.

command names  can seem tricky at first(ls,du,cat,df,grep and so on)

What are opetions
Options tell a command how to operate.
Options often begin with a dish or minux sign(like -e or -s)
Option are often represented by one letter or number


